<h2>Overview</h2><p>The installation of the Diabolical Inc Slipstream XLS in a 2015 Jeep Wrangler Unlimited JKU represents a game-changer in cargo security. As many Jeep owners know, having a reliable way to secure your gear while off-road or even in everyday situations is paramount, and the Slipstream XLS does just that. This tutorial outlines the steps to install this innovative system, ensuring you can keep your valuables safe without sacrificing functionality.</p><h2>What This Covers</h2><p>This guide will walk you through the key components, installation process, and tips to consider during the installation of the Slipstream XLS. By the end of this article, you'll be well-equipped to tackle this project confidently.</p><h2>Step-by-Step Breakdown</h2><ol><li><strong>Gather Your Tools and Parts:</strong> Before diving in, make sure you have all necessary tools and components. You'll need basic tools such as a wrench set, Phillips head screwdrivers, and possibly a torque wrench. Make sure to lay out your materials, including the Slipstream XLS kit, to ensure everything is easy to find.</li><li><strong>Remove Existing Cargo Setup:</strong> If you have an existing cargo cover or toolbox, remove these components first. The Slipstream XLS needs the space to fit securely against the back seat, utilizing all available cargo area.</li><li><strong>Install the Access Panel:</strong> Begin by installing the blocking panel that fits behind the driver’s side rear seat. This panel not only secures the cargo area but also includes an access point for easy retrieval of your items. Be meticulous about aligning the panel and securing it with the included hardware.</li><li><strong>Attach Wing Walls:</strong> The wing panels are crucial for the structural integrity and appearance of the Slipstream XLS. Carefully attach these panels according to the instruction manual, ensuring they fit snugly against the roll bar and follow the contour of the Jeep’s body.</li><li><strong>Secure Frame Rails:</strong> Install the upper frame rails, ensuring that they fit securely into place. These rails provide a sturdy framework for the entire system and allow for the stacking of additional gear.</li><li><strong>Fine-Tune and Secure All Components:</strong> Once all major components are in place, go back through and tighten all screws and fasteners. This includes the access panel, wing walls, and frame rails. A secure fit is essential for safety and functionality.</li></ol><h2>Helpful Tips</h2><ul><li>Read the instruction manual thoroughly before beginning the installation. Understanding the steps and components will save you time and frustration.</li><li>Use thread locker on all screws and bolts to prevent loosening over time, especially in off-road conditions.</li><li>Take your time with the alignment of parts. Everything should fit snugly but not require excessive force to install.</li><li>Consider removing the rear seat recline kit if you have one, as the Slipstream XLS works best without it.</li><li>As a final check, ensure all access points are functioning properly before closing up any panels.</li></ul><h2>Key Takeaways</h2><p>The Diabolical Inc Slipstream XLS is more than just a cargo cover; it is a comprehensive security solution for Jeep Wrangler owners. With thoughtful design and usability at its core, the installation process is straightforward if you follow the outlined steps. Secure your gear confidently and take full advantage of your Jeep's cargo space with this fantastic addition.</p>

